<body>

<p>The Song of the Feet</p>
    <br> 
<p>Is it appropriate that I sing</p>
    <br>
<p>The song of the feet</p> 
    <br>
    <br>
    <p>The weight of the body</p>
    <br>
    <p>And what the body chooses to bear</p>
    <br>
    <p>Fall on me</p>
    <br>
    <br>
    <p>I trampled the American Wilderness</p>
    <p>Forged frontier trails</p>
    <p>Outran the mom in Tulsa</p>
    <p>Got caught in Philadelphia</p>
    <br>
    <br>
    <p>And am still unreparated</p>
    <br>
    <br>
    <p>I soldier on in Korea</p>
    <p>Jungled through Vietnam sweated out Desert Store</p>
    <p>Caved my way through Afghanistan</p>
    <p>Tunneled the Worlds Trade Center</p>
    <br>
    <br>
    <br>
    <p>And on the worst day of my life</p>
    <br>
    <p>Walked behind JFK</p>
    <p>Shouldered MILK</p>
    <p>Stood Embracing Sister Beauty</p>
    <br>
    <br>
    <p>I wiggle my toes</p>
    <p>In the sands of time</p>
    <p>Trusting the touch that controls my motion</p>
    <p>Basking in the warmth of the embrace</p>
    <p>Day's end offers with warm salty water</p>
    <br>
    <br>
    <p>It is appropraite I sing</p>
    <p>The praise of the feet</p>
    <br>
    <br>
    <br>
    <p>I am a Black Woman</p>
    
    
    
</body>
